WEBVTT

00:02.000 --> 00:05.000
This programme contains
some strong language

00:05.040 --> 00:08.680
and scenes which some viewers
may find upsetting.

00:08.720 --> 00:11.040
EXPLOSION

00:12.480 --> 00:13.960
It was a lovely day.

00:14.000 --> 00:16.520
We'd been to the garden centre,
had lunch there,

00:16.560 --> 00:18.760
bought some nuts for the birds.
CAMERAS CLICK

00:18.800 --> 00:20.480
It was all very, very British.

00:23.200 --> 00:25.720
'You love your kids so much,
you think you'd know.'

00:25.760 --> 00:27.160
EXPLOSION

00:27.200 --> 00:29.200
'That, no matter where
they were in the world...

00:29.240 --> 00:31.280
GUNFIRE
'..3,000 miles away even,

00:31.320 --> 00:32.759
'you'd know.'

00:32.800 --> 00:35.480
You'd know if they were in danger.

00:35.520 --> 00:37.040
PHONE RINGS

00:40.520 --> 00:44.360
BIRDSONG,
PHONE CONTINUES

01:07.680 --> 01:09.240
WOMAN SIGHS

01:12.160 --> 01:14.400
CHATTER OUTSIDE

01:18.160 --> 01:19.760
Here we are.

01:19.800 --> 01:21.000
There.

01:24.240 --> 01:25.480
SHE SIGHS

01:29.680 --> 01:32.800
Nice cup of tea.
Ooh, I love this.Yeah.

01:34.360 --> 01:36.480
Summer Breeze
by The Isley Brothers

01:48.680 --> 01:51.400
MUSIC PLAYS,
PHONE RINGS

01:54.440 --> 01:57.120
Hello?'Hi, Sally, it's June.'
Oh, hi, June.

01:57.160 --> 01:59.520
JUNE INDISTINCT
Yeah, Reg's mum here.

01:59.560 --> 02:02.800
We've been out for lunch.'Did you
see the news? Six MPs killed.

02:02.840 --> 02:04.880
'It's on now.'

02:04.920 --> 02:05.920
Now?

02:07.840 --> 02:08.960
Thanks.

02:12.240 --> 02:13.640
MAGAZINES RUSTLE LOUDLY

