election night is about to begin.'

01:15:46.560 --> 01:15:48.720
..two, one.

01:15:48.760 --> 01:15:51.000
BUZZ OF CONVERSATION

01:15:53.000 --> 01:15:56.600
'Our star reporters are out
in the country at the key counts.

01:15:56.640 --> 01:15:59.440
'We've got our cameras
in all the places that matter.

01:15:59.480 --> 01:16:01.560
'At Sunderland South,
where they're just having

01:16:01.600 --> 01:16:03.440
'a final rehearsal
of getting the boxes in.

01:16:03.480 --> 01:16:06.560
'They plan to be
the first to declare.

01:16:06.600 --> 01:16:08.840
'At Portsmouth, Guildhall,

01:16:08.880 --> 01:16:11.680
'where the postal ballots are
being taken up the steps...'

01:16:21.680 --> 01:16:25.880
'..and at Enfield in London,
Tory target, the seat...'

01:16:29.360 --> 01:16:31.560
Excuse me

01:16:31.600 --> 01:16:33.360
That's a vote for Reg Keys.

01:16:33.400 --> 01:16:34.880
The Reg Keys pile is there.

01:16:34.920 --> 01:16:37.400
You put it on the
Tony bloody Blair pile! Excuse me?

01:16:38.680 --> 01:16:40.480
And that's the third time
you've done that,

01:16:40.520 --> 01:16:42.880
which I think is a bit much,
if you don't mind me saying so.

01:16:42.920 --> 01:16:45.600
What is it, Bob? That's the third
time he's put a vote for Reg Keys

01:16:45.640 --> 01:16:48.240
on the Tony Blair pile.
An honest mistake. Three times...

01:16:48.280 --> 01:16:50.840
An honest mistake... all Reg Keys,
all gone to Tony Blair!

01:16:50.880 --> 01:16:53.560
That's a level of consistency
that suggests something to me

01:16:53.600 --> 01:16:56.200
and what it suggests is a little
more than an honest mistake.

01:16:56.240 --> 01:16:59.560
If he says "honest mistake", Bob,
it was an honest mistake.

01:16:59.600 --> 01:17:03.600
Sally! How's it going?
I want you to do something for me.

01:17:03.640 --> 01:17:07.160
Hi, Richard. I'm going to get
somebody to watch this guy -

01:17:07.200 --> 01:17:09.000
that's going to take me
a couple of minutes -

01:17:09.040 --> 01:17:10.280
but for the next two minutes,

01:17:10.320 --> 01:17:14.040
you watch him and you watch
where he puts those votes, OK?

01:17:14.080 --> 01:17:15.520
Yeah, right. Thank you.

01:17:19.760 --> 01:17:21.680
Here is where we are.

01:17:21.720 --> 01:17:24.000
Newton Aycliffe.
We'll have done well here.

01:17:25.480 --> 01:17:29.800
There should be 1,423 votes
from this polling station.

01:17:29.840 --> 01:17:33.400
If it's under, that's fine, cos
some people go in and don't vote.

01:17:33.440 --> 01:17:35.120
But if it's over, that is not fine.

01:17:35.160 --> 01:17:38.160
That means some people have voted
more than once, so, if it's over,

01:17:38.200 --> 01:17:40.160
come and get me, all right?
Right.Thanks.

01:17:41.680 --> 01:17:44.720
'I've had a number of people saying
to me that they can't vote for me

01:17:44.760 --> 01:17:46.640
'because they were against
the war in Iraq.

01:17:46.680 --> 01:17:49.280
'Heaven knows what more
I could have done to convince them

01:17:49.320 --> 01:17:52.520
'that I also was opposed to the war
and, if it was like that for me,

01:17:52.560 --> 01:17:55.120
'it must have been
at least as strong for others...'

01:17:55.160 --> 01:17:57.400
'A personal
vote for you, you say,

01:17:57.440 --> 01:18:00.560
'but how much did your support for
the war count against you there?'

01:18:00.600 --> 01:18:03.200
'Well, that
became part of the issue,

01:18:03.240 --> 01:18:05.960
'especially within some
of the Asian communities,

01:18:06.000 --> 01:18:09.120
'but also amongst part
of the white community as well.'

01:18:10.720 --> 01:18:12.560
How are you doing, Bob?
BOB SIGHS

01:18:12.600 --> 01:18:15.560
I don't think we can win it.No.

01:18:15.600 --> 01:18:17.360
WOMEN LAUGH AND CHATTER

01:18:17.400 --> 01:18:19.800
Blair here? On his way.

01:18:19.840 --> 01:18:23.240
Where you going to put him?
In his room.

01:18:23.280 --> 01:18:26.440
Oh, you got him a room? Of course.
The candidates couldn't have one.

01:18:26.480 --> 01:18:28.840
We've been walking around here!
And you got him a room?

01:18:28.880 --> 01:18:30.200
He's got a country to run!

01:18:33.080 --> 01:18:36.360
Who are you going to allow to speak?
I haven't given it any thought.

01:18:36.400 --> 01:18:37.800
You've got the world's media here

01:18:37.840 --> 01:18:40.680
and haven't given any thought to
who's going to be allowed to speak?

01:18:40.720 --> 01:18:42.560
No, cos it all depends
on the result.

01:18:42.600 --> 01:18:45.600
Convention dictates
the top three will speak.

01:18:45.640 --> 01:18:47.000
What if we finish fourth?

01:18:47.040 --> 01:18:49.480
Well, someone's got to
finish fourth, haven't they?

01:18:49.520 --> 01:18:51.080
Reg?

01:18:51.120 --> 01:18:52.640
You've got to let Reg speak.

01:18:52.680 --> 01:18:55.080
If he finishes top three,
of course he can speak.

01:18:56.440 --> 01:18:58.760
Top three to speak.

01:18:58.800 --> 01:19:00.320
Right.

01:19:00.360 --> 01:19:02.160
He could finish fourth,
you know that.

01:19:02.200 --> 01:19:03.920
If that happens, he speaks.

01:19:03.960 --> 01:19:06.800
And the one who finishes fifth?
And the sixth?

01:19:06.840 --> 01:19:09.800
There's 15 candidates!
Monster Raving Loonies and worse.

01:19:09.840 --> 01:19:12.000
Do I let them all speak?
Do I turn it into a circus?

01:19:12.040 --> 01:19:13.880
I'm not asking you
to turn it into a circus,

01:19:13.920 --> 01:19:15.240
I'm talking about the top four.

01:19:15.280 --> 01:19:17.360
This is a four-horse race, this,
always has been -

01:19:17.400 --> 01:19:19.560
Labour, Tory, Lib Dem and Reg!

01:19:19.600 --> 01:19:22.400
The others are miles behind.
It would be totally wrong to stop

01:19:22.440 --> 01:19:25.240
any of the top four from speaking,
especially if it's this man here.

01:19:25.280 --> 01:19:28.200
I'm sticking with convention, Bob,
and the top three will speak.

01:19:28.240 --> 01:19:31.360
BOB SIGHS
You don't want to upset Tony. Not at all.

01:19:31.400 --> 01:19:34.120
I've kept a diary. Oh, yes? Yes.

01:19:34.160 --> 01:19:37.120
And I have listed every irregularity
that you have overseen

01:19:37.160 --> 01:19:41.000
in this campaign.Bob...
Every irregularity? Mm-hm.

01:19:41.040 --> 01:19:42.560
I wasn't aware there'd been one.

01:19:42.600 --> 01:19:45.040
Well, there was that business
with the electoral roll

01:19:45.080 --> 01:19:47.640
and how long it took us to get it.
You got it.Eventually.

01:19:47.680 --> 01:19:51.360
And then there was the map of the
constituency. Which you also got.

01:19:51.400 --> 01:19:54.360
Also eventually. And now you're
talking to me about convention.

01:19:54.400 --> 01:19:56.960
Well, convention states that
the candidates have a room

01:19:57.000 --> 01:19:59.520
where they can relax.
ALL the candidates, not just one.

01:19:59.560 --> 01:20:03.000
Are you about to say that you'll
overlook these "irregularities"

01:20:03.040 --> 01:20:04.440
if I agree to let this man speak?

01:20:04.480 --> 01:20:07.200
Because, if you say that, Bob,
you'll be out of here on your arse!

01:20:07.240 --> 01:20:09.400
In fact, you might even find
yourself in the nick!

01:20:09.440 --> 01:20:11.080
How dare you question my integrity?

01:20:11.120 --> 01:20:13.960
I have a run things as fair
and square as I possibly could!

01:20:14.000 --> 01:20:17.360
No-one is questioning
your integrity, are they, Bob?

01:20:19.080 --> 01:20:22.760
No.Three times, I've tried
to get Tony Blair to listen to me

01:20:22.800 --> 01:20:27.200
and three times, he's ignored me,
so I think he's got this coming!

01:20:27.240 --> 01:20:29.720
He's got to stand up there
with the world watching

01:20:29.760 --> 01:20:31.280
and he's got to listen to me.

01:20:31.320 --> 01:20:34.840
And that'll happen, as long as
you finish in the top three. Why?!

01:20:34.880 --> 01:20:37.520
Because convention dictates? Yes.

01:20:37.560 --> 01:20:39.560
Who sent us to war?

01:20:39.600 --> 01:20:41.040
It's not the people.

01:20:41.080 --> 01:20:42.840
They couldn't be convinced.

01:20:42.880 --> 01:20:45.880
But hundreds of
democratically elected MPs,

01:20:45.920 --> 01:20:48.920
they were. Mm-hm. Sticklers
for convention, all of 'em!

01:20:50.160 --> 01:20:51.720
I hope you get to speak, Reg.

01:20:55.120 --> 01:20:57.120
Convention!

01:20:57.160 --> 01:20:58.720
APPLAUSE AND CHEERING

01:20:58.760 --> 01:21:01.520
'We're seeing
pictures now of Tony Blair

01:21:01.560 --> 01:21:04.880
'arriving at the, er...
At his count, I believe.

01:21:04.920 --> 01:21:07.960
'Not clear what to
read into the Prime Minister's face.

01:21:08.000 --> 01:21:09.920
'He and Cherie going towards
the count there.

01:21:09.960 --> 01:21:12.320
'He's looking... He was looking
a bit

01:21:12.360 --> 01:21:15.600
'Putting a determined look
on his face and, er,

01:21:15.640 --> 01:21:18.600
'Cherie looking, again,
determinedly cheerful

01:21:18.640 --> 01:21:20.960
'as they go into the count,
wouldn't you say?'

01:21:24.960 --> 01:21:26.800
Here we go.

01:21:26.840 --> 01:21:29.280
4,252, Reg.

01:21:29.320 --> 01:21:32.320
Oh, that's wonderful, Reg!
That is wonderful!

01:21:32.360 --> 01:21:34.360
Where does that put us? Fourth.

01:21:38.600 --> 01:21:40.400
What's wrong?

01:21:40.440 --> 01:21:42.560
Only the top three speak.

01:21:42.600 --> 01:21:43.840
Oh, what?

01:21:45.200 --> 01:21:46.800
Who was third?

01:21:46.840 --> 01:21:48.960
Lib Dems. What did he get?

01:21:49.000 --> 01:21:52.760
Er, 4,935.That's practically a tie!

01:21:52.800 --> 01:21:55.120
No, it isn't, Bob.

01:21:55.160 --> 01:21:57.440
Who was fifth? Ukip.

01:21:57.480 --> 01:22:01.600
How many?646.OK, so we're just
behind third, well clear of fifth,

01:22:01.640 --> 01:22:03.600
and we still can't speak? Correct.

01:22:04.680 --> 01:22:06.080
Right, OK.

01:22:06.120 --> 01:22:09.040
The media are still upstairs,
so, once the declaration's over,

01:22:09.080 --> 01:22:12.520
we'll go up there and we'll tell
the world that you've been gagged.

01:22:12.560 --> 01:22:14.640
Labour, Tory and
the Lib Dems could speak -

01:22:14.680 --> 01:22:17.440
the people who sent us to war
could all speak -

01:22:17.480 --> 01:22:19.040
but Reg Keys couldn't.

01:22:20.640 --> 01:22:22.760
You must do as you see fit.

01:22:22.800 --> 01:22:24.480
Please, let me speak.

01:22:24.520 --> 01:22:25.840
Please?

01:22:27.080 --> 01:22:29.960
I'm not asking this for myself.
I'll be speaking...

01:22:30.000 --> 01:22:33.480
I won't even see Blair,
but the other families will see him.

01:22:33.520 --> 01:22:36.040
And the families of every
British soldier killed in Iraq,

01:22:36.080 --> 01:22:37.600
they'll see him.

01:22:37.640 --> 01:22:40.080
I don't think you should
stand in the way of that.

01:22:42.080 --> 01:22:44.320
You must excuse me.
I've got things I must do.

01:22:44.360 --> 01:22:46.480
'A rictus, rather
than genuine grin.

01:22:46.520 --> 01:22:48.520
'The last days of the campaign,

01:22:48.560 --> 01:22:51.360
'there's been a genuine grin on
his face. They thought they'd have

01:22:51.400 --> 01:22:53.760
'a really good night,
better than they're having so far.

01:22:53.800 --> 01:22:56.840
'Especially when talking about
their private life to the Sun.

01:22:56.880 --> 01:23:00.360
'Rather extraordinary. What? "Five
times a night Prime Minister?" '

01:23:00.400 --> 01:23:03.400
I, the returning officer
for the Sedgefield constituency,

01:23:03.440 --> 01:23:06.280
do hereby declare that the numbers
of votes in the election

01:23:06.320 --> 01:23:08.440
were as follows.

01:23:08.480 --> 01:23:11.320
Berony Abraham, 205...

01:23:12.560 --> 01:23:15.480
'When do you
most need compassion?

01:23:16.640 --> 01:23:18.600
'Probably at the point of death.

01:23:18.640 --> 01:23:22.320
'But when you die in war,
there is no compassion,

01:23:22.360 --> 01:23:26.920
'there's only hatred, because they
can't kill you unless they hate you.

01:23:28.360 --> 01:23:33.120
'So, no whispers from
a loving wife or mother...'

01:23:33.160 --> 01:23:35.280
GUNFIRE ECHOES
'Just your mates' screams

01:23:35.320 --> 01:23:39.080
'and your killer's snarling hatred.
That's the reality of war.'

01:23:39.120 --> 01:23:41.200
LOUD CRUNCH

01:23:41.240 --> 01:23:42.760
Six young men...

01:23:43.960 --> 01:23:46.960
'..dead in a filthy
storeroom-cum-toilet.

01:23:47.000 --> 01:23:50.000
'You multiply that
by 100,000, 200,000,

01:23:50.040 --> 01:23:53.320
'you add women and children,
and all on a lie?'

01:23:53.360 --> 01:23:55.680
CAMERAS CLICK All on a lie?

01:23:55.720 --> 01:23:59.440
..that Anthony Charles Lynton Blair
has been duly elected

01:23:59.480 --> 01:24:01.960
to serve as member for
the Sedgefield constituency.

01:24:02.000 --> 01:24:04.240
APPLAUSE AND SOME CHEERS

01:24:06.240 --> 01:24:08.120
LOUD CHEERS

01:24:12.840 --> 01:24:16.640
'..and I know too that Iraq has been
a divisive issue in this country.

01:24:18.040 --> 01:24:21.000
'But I hope now
that we can unite again

01:24:21.040 --> 01:24:23.680
'and look to the future,
there and here.'

01:24:23.720 --> 01:24:27.720
Our job is to serve people. That's
what I've tried to do in Sedgefield.

01:24:27.760 --> 01:24:30.000
It's what we'll try to do
for the country. Thank you.

01:24:30.040 --> 01:24:31.880
APPLAUSE AND CHEERING

01:24:40.840 --> 01:24:43.720
Right, ready to go?

01:25:00.560 --> 01:25:02.440
He's letting him speak.

01:25:02.480 --> 01:25:03.640
Richard!

01:25:10.760 --> 01:25:15.160
First of all, I would like
to thank the Returning Officer

01:25:15.200 --> 01:25:17.720
and all the people
who have worked hard

01:25:17.760 --> 01:25:19.640
to put all this together tonight.

01:25:20.880 --> 01:25:23.000
And I want to thank, in particular,

01:25:23.040 --> 01:25:29.320
all the fantastic people who have
organised and run this campaign

01:25:29.360 --> 01:25:32.440
and all the volunteers -
they've been tremendous.

01:25:34.120 --> 01:25:37.280
I'd also like to thank
my wife and my son

01:25:37.320 --> 01:25:38.960
for being here with me tonight,

01:25:39.000 --> 01:25:41.840
who have supported me tirelessly
through this campaign.

01:25:43.160 --> 01:25:45.360
A remarkable campaign.

01:25:45.400 --> 01:25:48.000
Er, I'm not...

01:25:48.040 --> 01:25:52.520
I don't claim to be
a professional politician.

01:25:52.560 --> 01:25:55.880
Fighting this campaign has not
been an easy task for me,

01:25:55.920 --> 01:26:00.800
but I had to do it
for my son, Thomas Keys,

01:26:00.840 --> 01:26:05.480
a Royal Military Policeman
killed in Iraq

01:26:05.520 --> 01:26:08.200
four days short
of his 21st birthday...

01:26:09.960 --> 01:26:14.200
..sent to war under extremely
controversial circumstances.

01:26:15.240 --> 01:26:18.680
Extremely controversial
circumstances.

01:26:18.720 --> 01:26:20.320
SMATTERING OF APPLAUSE

01:26:22.080 --> 01:26:25.920
If this war had been justified
by international law,

01:26:25.960 --> 01:26:29.080
I would have grieved,
not campaigned.

01:26:30.360 --> 01:26:34.520
If weapons of mass destruction
had been found in Iraq, again,

01:26:34.560 --> 01:26:38.280
I would have grieved,
not campaigned.

01:26:39.880 --> 01:26:42.800
And tonight,
there are lessons to be learned

01:26:42.840 --> 01:26:44.960
and I hope in my heart
that, one day,

01:26:45.000 --> 01:26:47.680
the Prime Minister
may be able to say sorry.

01:26:49.240 --> 01:26:51.600
That, one day,
you'll be able to say sorry

01:26:51.640 --> 01:26:55.800
to the families of the bereaved
and that, one day,

01:26:55.840 --> 01:27:00.360
the Prime Minister may be able to
visit wounded soldiers in hospital.

01:27:02.080 --> 01:27:05.400
Then our campaign
will not have been in vain.

01:27:07.120 --> 01:27:10.920
All the people who have
given me their vote tonight

01:27:10.960 --> 01:27:15.320
have sent a clear, resounding
message about the Iraq War.

01:27:15.360 --> 01:27:18.560
And thank you to all the people
who have voted for me tonight.

01:27:20.120 --> 01:27:21.880
And just finally...

01:27:23.880 --> 01:27:29.080
..I would like to dedicate
this campaign to all the brave 88,

01:27:29.120 --> 01:27:31.680
88 British servicemen,

01:27:31.720 --> 01:27:35.360
because some people do not know
how many have been killed.

01:27:37.200 --> 01:27:41.560
Servicemen who gave
their young lives in this conflict.

01:27:41.600 --> 01:27:43.760
APPLAUSE

01:27:46.920 --> 01:27:49.120
But may I just
in particular mention,

01:27:49.160 --> 01:27:51.440
as they've come to be known,
"The Six".

01:27:52.640 --> 01:27:59.800
Six Royal Military Policemen
left behind and slaughtered

01:27:59.840 --> 01:28:03.600
in a filthy police station
in al-Majar.

01:28:05.240 --> 01:28:06.480
My son...

01:28:08.680 --> 01:28:10.840
..Lance Corporal Tom Keys..

01:28:13.920 --> 01:28:15.520
'..Corporal Russell Aston...

01:28:19.040 --> 01:28:21.680
'..Corporal Simon Miller...

01:28:23.200 --> 01:28:25.480
'..Sergeant Simon Hamilton-Jewell...

01:28:27.880 --> 01:28:29.880
'..Lance Corporal Ben Hyde...

01:28:32.720 --> 01:28:34.680
'..and Corporal Paul Long.'

01:28:38.280 --> 01:28:39.840
May you rest in peace, lads.

01:28:40.880 --> 01:28:42.000
Thank you.

01:28:50.600 --> 01:28:53.800
APPLAUSE ECHOES THEN FADES
